# Origin Browser

A minimal, robust desktop web browser for Windows 10/11.  
Built with **C# WinForms + Microsoft Edge WebView2**.

## Why this stack?
- **No Rust/Node.js toolchain** – just the .NET 8 SDK.
- **Native WebView2** rendering (Chromium-based, preinstalled on Win11).
- **HTML/CSS/JS chrome UI** – customize the tabs and toolbar with web tech.
- **Small self-contained EXE** – ~35–45 MB single-file publish.
- **Real multi-tab architecture** – each tab is an isolated WebView2 instance.

## Features
- Multi-tab browsing (Ctrl+T new, Ctrl+W close, middle-click to close)
- Address bar with focus shortcut (Ctrl+L)
- Back / Forward / Reload / Home buttons
- Vim-style page scrolling: `j` / `k` (line), `Ctrl+d` / `Ctrl+u` (half-page), `g` / `G` (top/bottom)
- Navigation shortcuts: Ctrl+[/] or Ctrl+Left/Right
- Fullscreen toggle (F11)
- Dark theme across UI and tabs

## Prerequisites
- Windows 10 (1709+) or Windows 11
- WebView2 Runtime (already included with Windows 11; Windows 10 users likely have it via Edge updates)
- [.NET 8 SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0)

## Build & Run (from source)

```bash
cd OriginBrowser
dotnet build
dotnet run